Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the noodles.

When boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{125%g} to the water and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips, then chop into roughly 1cm pieces.

Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch} (stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the pepper and @sliced mushrooms{180%g}. Fry until slightly charred and soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Continue to stir while it cooks. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the garlic, lime zest and @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet} to the pan. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @soy sauce{25%ml}, @ketjap manis{25%g}, @mango chutney{80%g} and @water for the sauce{100%ml} to the pan.

Stir together, then add the @mangetout{80%g} and cook until the sauce has thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir the cooked noodles through the sticky sauce and toss until well combined.

Add a squeeze of lime juice.

Taste and season with salt, pepper and more lime juice if needed.

Share the sticky Thai style noodles between your bowls.

Sprinkle over the peanuts and coriander to finish.

Serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!